snippet.textDisplay:
Ok. I was just listening to Jhene's mixtape with the original couple days ago and this was always one of my favorite songs on it. I really like the way it was remixed, I like the way Future opens it up...a lot. Jhene and Miguel do just as good as the original if not seasonedly better. I don't especially like Future's verse in the middle, it's not bad, but this was a great song that had a mediocre verse from Gucci, the remix should have been blessed with a great verse and not a mediocre verse, it doesn't take too much away from it given that the vibe of this track is pretty damn dope, and probably a lot of people haven't heard the original and what better way to introduce them to it with an updated version. I didn't know what I was listening to when I first tapped the notification and I heard Future and the beat is banging given I can already hear Jhene over it and as soon as Miguel comes in it was like nostalgic, given I wasn't aware, like ohhh shii wuuut kinda a feeling. In that regard, at least for me not looking at the title, it was a nice surprise. I can't help to think what this song could have been had Future been able to provide more bars along the lines of his opening bars. Just my critical take on it. I still really enjoy the song.

Lastly, I just was reminded of a thought I had back then 2011/2012 as Jhene, Miguel, and Kendrick were coming to stardom (interestingly enough, Future as well). Jhene and Kendrick...amazing, Jhene and Miguel...amazing, Miguel and Kendrick...amazing. All out of Cali and I just always thought we would see more of them together which actually never happened. Kdot would have put this track overboard...and on constant repeat (I have listened to it about 5 times in the last 30 minutes). Can't help but to see the blue solo cups as a subtle shoutout to Nipsey, even if it wasn't meant to be.

ORIGINAL 9.5/10
Jhene 10
Miguel 10
Gucci Mane 6
Beat 10

REMIX 9/10
Jhene 10
Miguel 10
Future Opening 10
Future Verse 6
Beat and Variation from Original 11 (Amazed at how this sounds now 8 or 9 years later)
Missing Kendrick Lamar...Fail
Video 10 (Reminds me of great house parties back in the day, it feels genuine, like y'all actually got some drink in them cups during shooting, or y'all was shooting during a party. Spotlight on Mila J. Shoutouts to both audio and video producers on this, behind the scene heroes.
